🧪 1. Test Plan Overview

Project: Toreja Medical Clinic Website
Testing Type: UI Automation Testing
Tool: Selenium WebDriver with Python
Browsers: Chrome (primary), Firefox (secondary)
Test Type: Functional, UI, Navigation, Form Validation, Basic Security, Cross-browser

Objective:
Verify that all user-facing features of the clinic website work correctly, reliably, and consistently across browsers.

🏗️ 2. Scope of Testing

You will automate testing for:

Page loading & navigation
Links and buttons
Forms (especially contact/appointment)
Input validation
UI elements
Error handling
Responsiveness (basic)
Content visibility
Broken links/images
🚫 Out of Scope (for now)
Backend/database testing
Performance/load testing
API testing
Payment gateway (if any later)
🧭 3. Pages to Cover

Typical pages on a clinic website (confirm on site):

Home page
About Us
Services
Doctors/Staff
Contact Us
Appointment/Booking form
Navigation menu & footer

Each of these becomes a test module in your Selenium project.

✅ 4. High-Level Test Scenarios (Automatable)
A. Home Page Tests
ID	Test Scenario	Expected Result
TC_HM_01	Verify homepage loads	Title and main banner visible
TC_HM_02	Verify logo present	Logo displayed
TC_HM_03	Verify navigation menu links	All menu links clickable
TC_HM_04	Verify images load	No broken images
TC_HM_05	Verify footer links	All footer links work
B. Navigation Tests
ID	Test Scenario	Expected Result
TC_NAV_01	Click each menu item	Correct page opens
TC_NAV_02	Back/forward browser navigation	Works correctly
TC_NAV_03	URL validation	URL matches page
C. Services Page Tests
ID	Test Scenario	Expected Result
TC_SER_01	Services page loads	Heading visible
TC_SER_02	Services listed	All services visible
TC_SER_03	Links/buttons work	Navigate correctly
D. Contact / Appointment Form (VERY IMPORTANT)

This is the main automation focus.

ID	Test Scenario	Test Data	Expected Result
TC_FORM_01	Submit empty form	None	Validation errors shown
TC_FORM_02	Invalid email	test@	Error message
TC_FORM_03	Invalid phone	abc123	Error message
TC_FORM_04	Valid submission	Valid data	Success message
TC_FORM_05	Long input text	500 chars	Handled correctly
TC_FORM_06	Special characters	@#$%^	Handled/sanitized
TC_FORM_07	Required fields check	Partial data	Errors shown
E. UI Element Tests
ID	Test Scenario	Expected Result
TC_UI_01	Buttons visible	Displayed and clickable
TC_UI_02	Text alignment	Proper layout
TC_UI_03	Font/text visible	No overlap
TC_UI_04	Mobile view (resize window)	Layout adjusts
F. Broken Links & Images
ID	Test Scenario	Expected Result
TC_BL_01	Check all <a> tags	No 404 links
TC_BL_02	Check all <img> tags	No broken images

(You can automate this using requests + Selenium)

G. Basic Security Checks (Automation-friendly)
ID	Test Scenario	Expected Result
TC_SEC_01	Input script tags in form	Not executed
TC_SEC_02	SQL-like input ' OR 1=1	Handled safely
